Package org.usfirst.frc.team2220.robot

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Autonomous
    Autonomous utility functions.
    Piecing together these functions with different parameters allows for millions of different autonomous programs, if one is so inclined
    Currently utilizes the drivetrain, the collector and shooter
    Sensors used: Gyroscope, Camera
    Collector Deprecated
    This is an example of making an object where one really isn't needed because it is only used once
    Drivetrain
    Runs the drivetrain, simplifies commands so one can control all four wheels and all four modules very simply
    ImageProcessor
    Highly modified version of 2015 Vision Sample Program
    Currently boxes targets on an image, circles the brightest one, then gives statistics about location of the brightest target
    MacroPlayer
    Plays back stuff from MacroRecorder
    MacroRecorder
    2016 Macro, based off of last years at https://github.com/DennisMelamed/FRC-Play-Record-Macro Stores data from motors TODO add more motors than just drivetrain
    ModuleRotation
    Rotation for modules using abosulte encoders plugged into CANTalons
    Robot
    Main robot class.
    Defines everything and puts it to use somewhat efficiently.
    TwilightTalon
    Extension of TwilightTalon, primarily for check if current limits have been surpassed, and if they have, disabling the motor
    WheelRotation
    Runs a wheel using a PID loop.
    XBoxController
    The much needed extension of the inadequate Joystick class, XBoxController.
    Keeps track of button states and divides them into onPress, whileHeld, and onRelease.
    Only catch is that XBoxController.update() must be called once per loop
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    XBoxController.Button
    enum for all Button (not axes) types on xbox controller
    XBoxController.POV
    POV enum to treat the POV like a button
    XBoxController.TriggerButton
    Treats the triggers like a button, using 85% pressed as the boundary
